revision.text:
{{Documentation subpage}}
{{High-use}}
{{Template shortcut|wti}}

Useful in "External links" section, making a one-line navigation to Wiktionary. Not inline in the usual sense.

==Usage==
<code><nowiki>* {{Wiktionary-inline}}</nowiki></code> produces a link to the Wiktionary definition of the page title. '''Notice''': The first letter of each word is turned to lower case. Pass a parameter explicitly if it's not what you want.

<code><nowiki>* {{Wiktionary-inline|word}}</nowiki></code> Produces a link to '''word''' on Wiktionary:

* {{Wiktionary-inline|word}}

<code><nowiki>* {{Wiktionary-inline|word|Word}}</nowiki></code> Produces a link to '''word''' on Wiktionary, but titles the link '''Word''':

* {{Wiktionary-inline|word|Word}}

==See also==
=== Similar templates for other Wikimedia projects ===
{{Commons templates see also}}

=== Other templates linking to Wiktionary ===
{{Wiktionary templates common doc}}

==TemplateData==
{{TemplateDataHeader}}
<templatedata>
{
	"params": {
		"1": {
			"label": "term",
			"description": "the term to link to",
			"example": "word",
			"type": "line",
			"required": true
		},
		"2": {
			"label": "displayed text",
			"description": "text to render in the link to the wiktionary  entry",
			"example": "Word",
			"type": "line",
			"suggested": true
		},
		"extratext": {
			"label": "extra text",
			"description": "extra text to display after the link",
			"example": "sense #2",
			"type": "string"
		}
	},
	"description": "Adds an inline link to a given term, defaulting to BASEPAGENAME, on wiktionary",
	"format": "inline"
}
</templatedata>

<includeonly>{{Sandbox other||
[[Category:Wiktionary link templates]]
}}</includeonly>

